ldren with disabilities the opportunity to play as they want, as they wish, in an autonomous way. Establishing the goal of respecting the play for the sake of play of children with disabilities means building an authoritative, appropriate and competent area in favour of these children's needs. ABSTRACTING & INDEXING Evaluation of childrens' play is covered by the following services: Google Books Google Scholar Naviga (Softweco) Primo Central (ExLibris) ReadCube Semantic Scholar Summon (ProQuest) TDOne (TDNet) WorldCat (OCLC)  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 3.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 7aPSYCHOLOGY / General.2bisacsh  aPlay, playfulness, evaluation, assessment, observation, play-based.1 aBesio, Serenella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBianquin, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBulgarelli, Daniela, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBulgarelli, Daniela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaprino, Francesca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChâtelain, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKindler, Vardit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMolina, Paola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMuntean, Ana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRay-Kaeser, Sylvie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchneider, Eleanor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStancheva-Popkostadinova,